</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[212,333,1194,1218]" box="[212,333,1194,1218]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">
<emphasis box="[212,333,1194,1218]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[212,1172,1234,1386]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">
This species is named in honour of Maria Luiza M. Evangelista, who resides near the location where type-specimens were collected. In northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[943,1010,1266,1290]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Brazil</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authority="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista, 2010" authorityName="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista" authorityYear="2010" box="[1021,1129,1266,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1021,1129,1266,1290]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">M. luizae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is popularly known as “ 
<emphasis box="[539,657,1298,1322]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">soldadinho</emphasis>
” [“tiny trooper”/“tiny soldier”] or “ 
<emphasis box="[1067,1158,1298,1322]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">viuvinha</emphasis>
” [“little widow”], names that are also attributed to other resembling 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1047,1172,1330,1354]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Membracis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, like 
<taxonomicName box="[350,471,1362,1386]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimica">
<emphasis box="[350,471,1362,1386]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">M. mimica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
